# Interview Q&A - Marketing Professional

## Task Definition

### Objective
Generate 25–30 interview Q&A pairs for senior/director/VP Marketing roles assessing strategic judgment, analytical thinking, and practical execution.

### Context
- **Scope**: Real-world marketing challenges across 6 MECE domains (strategy, research, positioning, campaigns, analytics, growth)
- **Target audience**: Cross-functional leaders (Product, Sales, Finance) evaluating senior marketing candidates
- **Evidence standard**: Cite authoritative sources; acknowledge limitations and trade-offs

### Success Criteria
- All 17 validation checks PASS
- ≥70% questions test judgment (not recall)
- ≥70% answers include ≥1 citation; ≥30% include ≥2
- ≥50% answers acknowledge limitations/trade-offs
- Each topic cluster: ≥1 diagram + ≥1 table

### Constraints
- **Word count**: 150–300 per answer
- **Coverage**: MECE across 6 marketing domains
- **Language**: EN 50–70%, ZH 20–40%, Other 5–15%
- **Recency**: ≥50% sources <3 years (≥70% for digital/social)

### Assumptions
- Candidate accesses standard tools, public datasets, industry benchmarks
- Scenarios use realistic, anonymized data
- No proprietary information required

